  "body": "**Problem**\r\n\r\nIn the current version, the dropdown with users shows only contacts that were not added. Search results do not tell the group chat creator why the results are empty. There are some conditions that should be addressed in UI\r\n\r\n1. Query does not match any profile from users contacts\r\n2. Query returns a contact that has already been added to the group chat\r\n3. If performed by a member, the query returns a contact that has already been added to the group chat by the chat owner.\r\n\r\n**Solution**\r\n1. Do not exclude added contacts from the dropdown\r\n2. Use checkbox states to show differences between contacts\r\n3. Implement the error \"No contacts found\"\r\n\r\nCheckbox states for contacts\r\n1. Empty checkbox - contact can be added to the group chat\r\n2. Filled checkbox - contact just added to the member's input\r\n3. Filled disabled - the contact was already added to the group chat by someone else or the contact is a group chat owner. \r\n\r\n**Resources**\r\n\r\nFigma https://www.figma.com/file/17fc13UBFvInrLgNUKJJg5/Kuba%E2%8E%9CDesktop?node-id=21169%3A484598&t=55mHIhpgmCcfCUH3-1\r\n\r\nVideos\r\nFor an owner https://vimeo.com/771521832\r\nFor a member https://vimeo.com/771522889\r\n \r\n",
